title: Bone Bender Mountain Bike Challenge
description: The Bone Bender returns to Clinton Lake State Park for our 6th Annual event.  New this year is our distance events including the Marathon race (60K+). Come challenge yourself  and enjoy some of the sweetest trails in the Midwest.  Party with your friends and just have a grand old time riding your bike.
course: The loop course (50K to 60K depending on final course used)  is comprised of single track trails, rocky technical sections, short power climbs.  Several areas will cross rocky stream beds while other areas will have fast flowing sections.  All this along  the  North Shore of Clinton Lake which is ranked  among the best trail systems in the Midwest.
registration:
Early registration fees: $25.00 Short Course, $40.00 for Full Bone Bender, $50.00 per team. 
Registration fees after 3/1/14: $35.00 Short Course, $50.00 for Full Bone Bender, $60.00 per team. 
Race day fees (if not sold out): $45.00 Short Course, $60.00 for Full Bone Bender, $70.00 per team. 

Entry fee includes T-shirts (must be registered by 4/1/14) , fully stocked aid stations and post race refreshments and $3.00 for insurance.  

Note: A USA Cycling license is required.  If you are not an annual license holder then a One day licenses can be purchased  for $10.00.
directions: I-70 - take from KC (traveling West), to exit # 197 - the Lecompton exit.  There well be a brown sign with white letters that says Clinton & Perry Lake)  Take Hwy 10 East  (South)  to the Clinton Parkway Exit.  At the bottom of the exit ramp turn right at the stop sign, take another right at the  dead end, then take the second left  on 1415 Road (Park Entrance).   Follow signs to the Swim Beach

Wyco's Revenge Mountain Bike Race
description:
Welcome to the 3rd Annual Wyco’s Revenge Mountain Bike Race. Come challenge yourself to the full Wyco’s Revenge or one of our  two shorter course opens Wyco’s Revenge Lite and Wyco’s Revenge Sprint  With all events you get to enjoy a fabulous evening of riding the super fun Wyandotte County Lake Parks trails and hanging out with your friends.

What is it?: The Wyco’s Revenge is a mountain bike event held on off-road single track trails. The event will challenge participants both physically and mentally.  The final laps of the Wyco’s Revenge will require lights. Full distance participants will complete 4 laps for a total of 60 kilometers miles.  The Wyco’s Revenge Lite will complete 2 laps.  The Wyco’s Sprint will complete 1 lap.  No lights are required for the Wyco Sprint or the Wyco Lite.
course: Course Details:  The current course distance is 9+miles.  Course includes flowing single track, double track, gravel roads, a log crossing or two, and a few minor technical sections.  The course is very beginner friendly. The course is comprised of rolling terrain along Wyandotte County Lake.  Bring out your single speed and you will flow like a pro!

A USA Cycling license or one-day license is required.
directions: Directions to the Venue: I-70 to 435 North,  take the Leavenworth Rd exit East.  Proceed to the main park entrance which is N 83rd ST.  Left into park on N 83rd ST.  Left onto County Lake Rd, Right onto East Drive, Left at the sign that says shelter 3,5 & 7.  Proceed to shelter 3.
